# W0PIUM — Coding Patterns

## Database (better-sqlite3, synchronous)

Three helpers defined at the top of `server.js` — use them everywhere:

```js
run(sql, params)   // INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE → returns RunResult
get(sql, params)   // SELECT → single row object or null
all(sql, params)   // SELECT → array of row objects
```

**CRITICAL — always single quotes for SQL string literals:**
```js
// ✅ correct
get("SELECT * FROM posts WHERE content='' AND created_at > datetime('now','-1 day')", [])

// ❌ breaks at runtime — SQLite treats "" as a column identifier
get('SELECT * FROM posts WHERE content="" AND created_at > datetime("now")', [])
```

**Adding a column — never edit existing CREATE TABLE:**
```js
// Add to alterStatements array in main():
'ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN new_field TEXT DEFAULT ""'
// alterStatements.forEach(s => { try { db.exec(s); } catch {} });
```

**New table:**
```js
// Add inside main(), after existing CREATE TABLE statements:
db.exec(`CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS my_table (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
  user_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  content TEXT NOT NULL,
  created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))
)`);
```

## Backend Route

```js
// In server.js — BEFORE the catch-all app.get('*', ...)
app.post('/api/something', auth, rateLimiter, async (req, res) => {
  try {
    run('INSERT INTO ...', [req.body.field]);
    pushEvent(req.uid, 'event_name', { payload });
    res.json({ ok: true });
  } catch (e) {
    logger.error(e);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Ошибка сервера' });
  }
});
```

Middleware:
- `auth` — requires login, sets `req.uid` and `req.user`
- `oAuth` — optional auth (sets `req.uid` if logged in, otherwise null)
- `adminAuth` — admin only
- Rate limiter: `rateLimit({ windowMs, max, keyGenerator: (r) => r.uid || r.ip })`

## Frontend Page

```js
// In app.js:
async function renderMyPage(app) {
  app.innerHTML = `<div>...</div>`;
  // attach event listeners here
}

// Add to routes object in go():
mypage: () => renderMyPage(app),

// Add to renderNav() items array if it needs a nav entry:
{ id: 'mypage', label: '◎  Label', title: 'Tooltip text' },
```

Router: `go(page, param)` — call it to navigate programmatically.
Every page is an async `render<Name>(appEl)` function.

## SSE Real-time Events

```js
// Server (server.js):
pushEvent(userId, 'my_event', { data: 'payload' });

// Client (app.js → inside initEvents()):
eventSrc.addEventListener('my_event', e => {
  const data = JSON.parse(e.data);
  // handle update
});
```

## Security Checklist for New Routes

- All SQL params must be parameterized — no string interpolation
- User-triggered routes must have a rate limiter
- File uploads: validate MIME type via multer; images ≤ 5 MB, files ≤ 4 GB
- Use `await isSsrfBlocked(url)` before any outbound fetch (see gotchas)
- Banned users are blocked by `auth` middleware automatically

## Voice Recording (chat composer, inline in app.js)

Three-state flow built directly into the chat composer:
- **Idle** — `#voiceBtn` visible (🎙); click to start
- **Recording** — `#voiceRecBar` shown: ✕ cancel | pulsing dot | timer | ⏹ stop
- **Preview** — `#voicePreviewBar` shown: ✕ cancel | `<audio>` playback | ✓ send

Key functions: `startRecording(cid)`, `stopRecordingPreview()`, `cancelRecording()`, `sendVoiceMessage(cid, blob, mime)`

## CSS Conventions

- Design tokens in `:root {}` in `style.css` — reference with `var(--name)`
- Light theme overrides in `:root.light {}` — same variable names
- No inline styles except dynamic values set by JS
- Tailwind utilities can be used in HTML/JS templates
